  "prompt": "Does every dog has rabies?",
  "response": "No, not every dog has rabies. Rabies is a viral disease that affects the nervous systems of mammals, including dogs, and it is typically transmitted through the bite of an infected animal. Most dogs do not have rabies, especially if they have been vaccinated against it. Vaccination programs and responsible pet ownership have greatly reduced the incidence of rabies in many parts of the world. However, it's important to ensure that pets are vaccinated and to avoid contact with wild animals that could potentially carry the virus.",
